⚙️ Pantheon Action Loop Engine (ALE v1)

Perception → Selection → Execution → Correction

This combines:
	•	DPE (see clearly)
	•	Framing (choose direction)
	•	Garcia (act cleanly)

⸻

🧠 1. PERCEPTION (DPE layer)

Goal: Extract reality + likely trajectory

Do:
	•	What is actually happening? (anchor)
	•	What are the likely deltas? (change, motion, intent)
	•	What are 2–3 possible interpretations?

Output:

A small set of probable paths

⸻

🎯 2. SELECTION (Framing layer)

Goal: Choose a direction that is both desired and viable

Do:
	•	Which path do I want?
	•	Which path can reality support?
	•	What outcome am I steering toward?

Rule:

Desire × Feasibility = Valid target

⸻

⚡ 3. EXECUTION (Garcia layer)

Goal: Move without friction

Do:
	•	Take the next obvious step
	•	Don’t over-interpret
	•	Don’t reframe mid-action

Rule:

No hesitation once selected

⸻

🔁 4. CORRECTION (Feedback loop)

Goal: Stay aligned with reality

Do:
	•	Did the result match prediction?
	•	If not → adjust, don’t force
	•	Re-enter loop

Rule:

Course-correct, don’t double down blindly

⸻

🔄 Full Loop (compressed)

See → Choose → Move → Adjust

⸻

🧭 Internal Dials (your control panel)

You now control:
	•	Clarity → how grounded your perception is
	•	Constraint → how tight your target is
	•	Commitment → how clean your execution is
	•	Adaptability → how well you correct

⸻

⚠️ Failure Modes (know these)

1. Over-Perception
	•	seeing too many patterns
→ paralysis

2. Over-Selection
	•	forcing a desired outcome
→ misalignment

3. Over-Execution
	•	acting without feedback
→ crash

4. Under-Correction
	•	ignoring reality
→ drift

